review_blob: Grassy smell.  Im fond of the bitter taste. Easily accessible.  Not bad. A good ocasional buy.

Typical Miller swill.  No taste, horrid 
port-a-john smell.  If you must buy Millers, get Highlife or Beast Ice.

Reeks of rice.  For me, thats the worst thing about this beer.  Taste is bland, unoffensive.  Aftertaste is slightly metallic (not near the extent of MGD).    Compared to mega american brews, this is up there.  Otherwise, its not that good. Cheap, unoffensive, 5.5% alcohol...good for those lean weeks between pays for po folks like me.

Better than MGD.  About the same as Miller Lite.  Not a great brew by any stretch.  Tastes of corn and smells like peas and carrots.  I can tolerate it because its cheap.  1.39 for a 40oz.  If you are going for a cheap american mega, not a bad choice.  As Miller products go, Id still choose the Beast.
Vilest of the vile.  Id honestly rather drink the water you see on those feed the children commercials.  Very rancid, metallic taste.

Drinkable beer.  Go for this one over Amber Bock or Killians.  Doesnt have the foul aftertaste of Michelob products, and as my brother describes Killians "Tastes Like Vomit"...well said concerning all Coors swills.
